{"cursor":"45889","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{multiple issues|\n\n\n}}\n\n\n'Elementary arithmetic' is the simplified portion of arithmetic which includes\nthe operations of addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division.\n\nElementary arithmetic starts with the natural numbers and the written symbols\n(digits) which represent them. The process for combining a pair of these numbers\nwith the four basic operations traditionally relies on memorized results for\nsmall values of numbers, including the contents of a multiplication table to\nassist with multiplication and division.\n\nElementary arithmetic also includes fractions and negative numbers, which can be\nrepresented on a number line.\n\nThe abacus is an early mechanical device for performing elementary arithmetic,\nwhich is still used in many parts of Asia. Modern calculating tools which\nperform elementary arithmetic operations include cash registers, electronic\ncalculators, and computers.\n","linknr":256,"url":"Elementary_arithmetic","recorded":1362686414,"links":35,"instances":["mathematics","punctuation","number","number","mathematics","number","number","arithmetic","number","number","number","punctuation","number","punctuation","symbol","number"],"pdf":["http://math.coe.uga.edu/TME/Issues/v10n2/5ross.pdf","http://math.coe.uga.edu/TME/Issues/v10n2/5ross.pdf","http://www.alfons-kolling.de/schule/Rechen-U-Boot-en.pdf"],"categories":["Elementary arithmetic|*","Mathematics education"],"headings":["The digits","Addition","Successorship and size","Counting","Subtraction","Multiplication","Division","Educational standards","See also","Further reading","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/f4/Ambox_content.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/f/f2/Edit-clear.svg/40px-Edit-clear.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a4/Text_document_with_red_question_mark.svg/40px-Text_document_with_red_question_mark.svg.png","//upload.wikimed